message.content:
If under the given weather conditions 10 pairs of socks dried in 10 hours, then the drying time is independent of the number of pairs of socks (assuming there is enough space and airflow for all socks to dry simultaneously without any interference from each other). Therefore, seven pairs of socks would also take the same amount of time to dry as 10 pairs under identical conditions.

So, it will take Tom **10 hours** to dry seven pairs of socks.
